Class UnitType

java.lang.Object
model.UnitType
public class UnitType extends Object
Represents a flat unit type within a BTO project, tracking total units, available/unbooked units, and pricing.

Provides operations to assign/unassign units and adjust availability.

Since:
24/4/2025
Version:
final
Author:
FCSH Group 2

    • UnitType

      public UnitType(String type, int totalUnits, double price)
      Constructs a new UnitType with specified name, total units, and price. Initializes both availableUnits and unbookedUnits to totalUnits.
      Parameters:
      type - the flat type name
      totalUnits - the total number of units for this type
      price - the price per unit

      public boolean assignUnit()
      Attempts to assign (reserve) one unit of this type.
      Returns:
      true if a unit was successfully assigned; false if none left

    • unassignUnit

      Attempts to unassign (release) one previously assigned unit.
      Returns:
      true if a unit was successfully unassigned; false if at max
